20 Oct 2018 15:18






Necroposting is a bit vaguely defined at the moment, but historically we consider necroposting to essentially be when people respond to very old discussion threads or lines of discussion within a page but without actually advancing the discussion. Examples of necroposting are like Dr Santi's posts above - they are considered necroposting because although he is responding to criticisms, those criticisms were posted so long ago that the people he is responding to will likely never see them. He is effectively not advancing the discussion because that discussion was made six years ago. It is rather like going to a book club the day after the meeting and trying to talk - you can do it, but nobody is there to listen to you and you're just making noise.







